flowRoot.flowPara: Once the nosecone and rocket have been mechanically separated by the NSR, there is still a need to push the two pieces far enough apart to expose the Drogue chute to air. The Pusher Assembly includes a hollow tube that is tied off with surgical tubing to a support ring that is attached to the nosecone. When loaded the tubing is cocked and puts about 200 N of force on the recovery assembly.
